The age distribution differs significantly by class While each class follows a somewhat symmetrical pattern (since the Mean and Median are close), the location of the distribution changes There is a clear hierarchy in age across classes.
the median age in 1st Class is 36.5, in 2nd Class is 30, and in 3rd Class is 25

While 96% of 1st-class women survived, only 50% of 3rd-class women survived. Among men, the survival rate was very low, especially in 3rd class (15%).
